    "question_id": "Q1",
    "framework": "CAIQ",
    "text": "Are audit and assurance policies, procedures, and standards established, documented, approved, communicated, applied, evaluated, and maintained?"
  },
  "outbound_response": "Yes. BNY Mellon's management, including the Chief Executive Officer and Chief Financial Officer, with participation by the members of the Disclosure Committee, has responsibility for ensuring that there is an adequate and effective process for establishing, maintaining, and evaluating disclosure controls and procedures designed to ensure that information required to be disclosed in SEC reports is timely recorded, processed, summarized, and reported, and that such information is accumulated and communicated to management to allow timely decisions regarding required disclosure [span:edgar:bny-mellon-corp:0001390777-23-000033::Item_16#0009]. These responsibilities are likewise reflected in prior periodic filings, evidencing that the framework is documented, applied, and consistently maintained over time [span:edgar:bny-mellon-corp:0001390777-22-000043::Item_16#0006]. With respect to external audit governance, the Audit Committee has established pre-approval policies and procedures applicable to all services provided by our independent registered public accountants, consistent with SEC rules, using both class pre-approval and specific pre-approval approaches for audit and permitted non-audit services [span:edgar:bny-mellon-corp:0001193125-25-046216::Item_3#0154]. Collectively, these arrangements demonstrate that audit and assurance policies, procedures, and standards are established, documented, approved, communicated, applied, evaluated, and maintained.",
